VectorExpr.Name: VectorExpr
Comments: Represents both instant and range vectors

Factories.Name: Abs
Comments: Returns the input vector with all sample values converted to their absolute value.

Factories.Name: Absent
Comments: Returns an empty vector if the vector passed to it has any elements (floats or native histograms) and a 1-element vector with the value 1 if the vector passed to it has no elements.
This is useful for alerting on when no time series exist for a given metric name and label combination.

Factories.Name: quantile_over_time
Comments: Calculates the φ-quantile (0 ≤ φ ≤ 1) of the values in the specified interval.
